    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family containing 44 genera and around 760 species of primarily herbaceous plants, but the family also includes some woody shrubs and a genus of small tropical trees. All species in the family have bisexual, regular, dish-shaped flowers with one superior pistil (female structure) and many stamens (male parts). The buds and flowers are usually large and often nodding.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
